# For Google Calendar API
# You need to create a project in Google Cloud Console, enable the Google Calendar API,
# and create credentials (OAuth 2.0 Client IDs).
# Download the credentials.json file and place it in your project directory.
# The first time you run the bot, you will be prompted to authorize the application.
# A token.json file will be created to store the access and refresh tokens.
# Make sure to add credentials.json and token.json to your .gitignore file.
GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS="./credentials.json"
